{"source_key":"sha256-c8597aca71664a84bdd657ea13dadbd3","record_index":539,"record_hash":"sha256:51f353770582aab89759ddcf2383e9c685e9b14ecdf6db4f4a43bc2fe1cad641","timestamp":"2026-05-20T01:48:16.076Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: ce515e\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 469\nOutput:\nThe index is not the association. It is a disposable acceleration structure.\nIf the heuristic changes, rebuild the index and old sessions can benefit\nretroactively.\n\nFor v1, write only branch, review, and change indexes:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agentlog-index-version = 1\ngitbutler:agentlog-index:branch:<branch-key> = set<session-key/turn-key>\ngitbutler:agentlog-index:review:<review-key> = set<session-key/turn-key>\ngitbutler:agentlog-index:change:<change-id> = set<session-key/turn-key>\n```\n\nThe index value includes both the session key and turn key so an index lookup can\nresolve directly to the owning session without scanning session turn lists.\nBranch and review index key material should be safe for GitMeta keys; hashing\nbranch/review values is acceptable as long as the readable values remain in the\nturn snapshot. Change ids are already compact, durable identifiers and can be\nused directly unless the GitMeta key rules require escaping.\n\nDo not write a path index in v1. Path-level keys can explode with large commits,\nbroad worktree changes, generated files, or dependency lockfile churn. File\npaths remain in the turn observations for scoring after branch/review/change\ncandidate discovery.\n\nAdding indexes is not a large GitMeta model cost if they remain derived lookup\nkeys. The real costs are write amplification, stale-index rebuild behavior, key\nexplosion, sync bloat, and making sure readers do not treat\n`agentlog-index:*` as durable association truth.\n\nFor a branch-name query, lookup can start from turns where that branch was\nobserved in the stack/branch snapshot, then boost turns where commits on that\nbranch matched files from a previous worktree snapshot.\n\nFor a PR/review-id query, lookup can start from turns where a branch carried\nthat review identifier, then optionally expand through the PR branch, head\ncommits, change ids, and touched paths.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T01:48:16.076Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}